Almost time to cross over into 2023. I am so grateful to have had such an incredible year in music. I got to play with the best musicians alive today on the best albums that came out this year. I also took on a challenge to listen to 1001+ albums within the year.  In the pictures are some of the records released in 2022 that were important to me. Happy New Year! Love peace and positivity to all! #1001recordsyoumusthearbeforeyoudie #musicformyages
What an amazing night celebrating @klosetyler and his future with @brianna_campo We love you Tyler.

Davenport Cabinet “Our Machine” turns 10 years old today! This record represents a whole other era of our life. But, somehow, every song is still relevant to me today. Thanks to @cyndifferous over at @evilinkrecords we now have the updated version of this record on all streaming platforms. Finally the way myself @klosetyler & @rorylh intended it to be heard. All the sounds from family and friends on this record made it the most special. Two of my favorite moments are the vocals of @tsaggs on “Simple Worlds” & the vocals of @youshouldwriteabook on “Dancing on Remains”. “Black Dirt Burden” was the first time @tomfarkas played bass on a Dav Cab song before becoming the permanent bass player. @cathystever provided the cover art and @jrvanguardtattoo the back. @skystever facilitating and creating all sorts of art and visuals. On the @coheed tours following this release @weerd_science @zacharyacooper & @claudiopsanchez supported and helped me in performing early entree versions of the title track “Our Machine”. And of course @blzjames helped me promote it. It was a magic time of love and support. Link will to the album will be in bio for next couple of days. #davenportcabinet #ourmachine

The second line of this #DavenportCabinet song is “Another two men lost at sea”. I am thinking it would be fitting to play it on the @ssneverender 🤷🏻‍♂️ For those unfamiliar Davenport Cabinet was what I called the music room I had in our house in Warwick, NY. People would often say they thought it was a haunted room. I decided to name it after the Davenport brothers spirit cabinet magic show. They would convince people within their magic cabinet spirits would play musical instruments. I’m the summer of 2013 @klosetyler came over and we recorded this version of our song “Drown it All”. 10 years ago 😳 Thanks to @nicklospinuso who filmed and edited we were able to track this footage down. It makes me miss the room and it’s creative energy so much. Countless @coheed guitar parts, Dav Cab songs, and other musical ideas were created in that room. We will be channeling its energy when we play on the boat in October. Let us know what other #DavenportCabinet songs you suggest we play on the #ssneverender 
Link to the album Our Machine is in my bio.

- [x] Exiting my flight at JFK the pilot looked at me and said “Your Done!” Yes @lsdunes tour is over. Our incredible team made it a fantastic run. A magical tour came to an end. But… I am by no means done. Something became very clear to me during the lockdown. If I am lucky enough to make a living creating music & playing it live then I should take any opportunity that seems appealing to do so. In doing that I am only better and more useful in all collaborations I am involved in. Breaks are good. I am tired. I need to be with my family. I need… Beach time! I will now shut down a bit and tune out. But in no way am I done. @coheed starts rehearsals for the second leg of #noworldforthewakingmindtour in less than 3 weeks. By then I will be ready to get back to the best job in the world. Thank you for all the love and support in this journey.

‘Old Wounds’ is officially out now and available everywhere. This was the second song @lsdunes recorded out in Joshua Tree at @ranchodelalunastudio with @alexnewps. #journeyofariff 🎥#1 is me playing into my 1959 @fender 5E3 Tweed deluxe combo amp for the first time. The riff I play is the verse to the newest @lsdunes song “Old Wounds”. I bought this amp with the intentions of using it on a song at the @ranchodelalunastudio sessions we did with @alexnewps It was clear immediately at this moment that amp should be used on “Old Wounds”. @itookthisphoto & @russo315 knew just how to get the best sounds from it. We set it up with a mic in that bathroom shower. 🎥#2 is the morning before tracking “Old Wounds”. A beautiful desert morning with the sounds of @anthonygreen666 warming up in song in the distance. The last photo I took just after tracking my main guitars. If you have not heard the song #oldwounds yet the link is in my bio. #lsdunes 🎥#1 @evan_heavy

Surprise! To celebrate the 1 year anniversary of ‘Past Lives’ @lsdunes are so excited to announce that we are releasing the deluxe version, ‘Lost Songs: Lines and Shapes’ on November 10th. This release is the best way we know how to celebrate the anniversary of our band’s debut full length album. Just like our first release off of ‘Past Lives’ the demo version of ‘Permanent Rebellion’ is now yours.

“included here is the blueprint to how Past Lives came to be. the spark of each song as we started this journey to each triumphant end. Lines and Shapes will take the listener down the same path we traveled as a band. listen in on how we created together from afar. sending digital breadcrumbs back and forth, building foundations for what was to come in the cloud, and then finally to those structures built in their definitive form.
Lines and Shapes not only celebrates the anniversary of Past Lives, but also the craft of songwriting and the many dynamics of what it means to be in a band. it is something i wish i was able to purchase for every record i ever loved and wondered how did this come to be” - @frankieromustdie 

Art by: @gordondouglasball

As soon as we started recording Old Wounds we knew we wanted to release the demo as well. You’ll now get the chance to hear it as we did from the very beginning. Old Wounds (Demo) will be yours October 27th 🧡
